241
00:17:27,348 --> 00:17:28,973
But what if they've done something to her?

242
00:17:29,012 --> 00:17:30,538
She's going to be all right!

243
00:17:30,579 --> 00:17:32,008
Made a call already.

244
00:17:40,528 --> 00:17:44,105
Hi, Abby. How've you been?

245
00:17:44,142 --> 00:17:46,214
Suzanne. I'm good. How are you?

246
00:17:46,253 --> 00:17:48,522
Good, good. And your daughter--
She must be starting school--

247
00:17:48,557 --> 00:17:52,101
She's good. I'm so sorry.
I'm in such a rush. I'll see you later, ok?

248
00:17:52,140 --> 00:17:53,633
Sure, sure. Have a good day now.

249
00:18:02,536 --> 00:18:03,965
What are you doing? Huh?

250
00:18:04,008 --> 00:18:06,593
- I'm calling the cops.
- No! You cannot call the cops.

251
00:18:06,631 --> 00:18:10,208
- Babe, babe, he's right there. He's--
- We have to do exactly what he says.

252
00:18:10,245 --> 00:18:12,416
- But I just thought--
- No, listen to me.

253
00:18:12,453 --> 00:18:16,227
Just calm down. Let's go.

254
00:18:19,650 --> 00:18:23,032
- Is that everything?
- Yes, of course it's everything.

255
00:18:23,073 --> 00:18:27,828
What, you think I'm going to risk Sophie's
life for the sake of a few bucks?

256
00:18:27,871 --> 00:18:33,052
- You just did.
- Oh, Jesus Christ. Abby.

257
00:18:33,086 --> 00:18:34,580
I'm sorry.

258
00:18:36,125 --> 00:18:38,066
Let's just get it over with.

259
00:18:39,420 --> 00:18:41,841
- Hi, how are you?
- Hi.

260
00:18:41,883 --> 00:18:43,377
I'd like to make a withdrawal.

261
00:18:46,490 --> 00:18:48,726
Um... I'm going to need some I.D.

262
00:18:48,761 --> 00:18:50,484
Sure.

263
00:18:53,367 --> 00:18:55,188
What do you need him for?

264
00:18:55,223 --> 00:18:57,044
Well, it's just that it's a very large amount--

265
00:18:57,078 --> 00:18:59,019
Yeah, it's a large amount,
but it's our money, isn't it?

266
00:18:59,061 --> 00:19:01,711
- Of course, sir.
- Then just do it!

267
00:19:01,749 --> 00:19:05,392
Stop it. Listen to me. You're going
to blow this whole thing, all right?

268
00:19:05,427 --> 00:19:08,460
Just for Sophie.
Just go back to the car.

269
00:19:09,650 --> 00:19:10,598
OK?

270
00:19:14,321 --> 00:19:15,465
I'm sorry.

271
00:19:19,534 --> 00:19:23,494
I'm sorry. My husband's under
a lot of pressure right now, so...

272
00:19:41,799 --> 00:19:43,871
You're not too good
in a crisis, are you, Neil?

273
00:20:03,200 --> 00:20:05,501
Shit!

274
00:20:10,622 --> 00:20:12,344
Is there a problem here?

275
00:20:12,381 --> 00:20:14,387
Uh...

276
00:20:17,531 --> 00:20:20,247
- No, officer....
- OK, then move it.

277
00:20:20,283 --> 00:20:22,289
- Yeah, I'm just waiting--
- Move it now.

278
00:20:22,329 --> 00:20:23,539
Excuse me. Sorry.

279
00:20:34,870 --> 00:20:37,454
Cash and cards now.

280
00:20:37,493 --> 00:20:40,361
- Chop, chop. Give us your purse.
- Wallet.

281
00:20:42,291 --> 00:20:45,672
Straight across here.
Straight across right here.

282
00:20:45,714 --> 00:20:48,266
It's over now, OK?
You've got what you want.

283
00:20:48,305 --> 00:20:50,857
- Now give us back our daughter.
- That's every cent we have.

284
00:20:53,103 --> 00:20:55,721
Well, let's just check it, shall we? Eh?

285
00:20:55,758 --> 00:20:56,706
Uhh.

286
00:21:07,659 --> 00:21:10,025
What are you doing?
What the hell are you doing?

287
00:21:10,058 --> 00:21:11,715
You could say...

288
00:21:11,753 --> 00:21:14,306
I've got money to burn.

289
00:21:14,344 --> 00:21:16,253
Neil! Why are you doing this?

290
00:21:16,296 --> 00:21:17,343
- Jesus!
- Please don't! Stop!

291
00:21:17,383 --> 00:21:20,611
- Christ, what are you, crazy?
- Stop it! Stop it!

292
00:21:20,647 --> 00:21:22,751
My money! What the hell are you doing?

293
00:21:22,789 --> 00:21:25,985
Please stop! Please! Please!

294
00:21:26,020 --> 00:21:27,678
That's our money burning!

295
00:21:30,467 --> 00:21:33,313
- Stop it!
- For Christ's sake!

296
00:21:36,161 --> 00:21:38,232
- Neil.
- God!

297
00:21:39,296 --> 00:21:41,597
- Left. Go left.
- Oh, my God.

298
00:21:49,852 --> 00:21:53,746
Oh, my God.

299
00:21:57,370 --> 00:21:58,614
Oh, my God.

300
00:22:01,753 --> 00:22:05,265
People are going to be wondering
where you are right now, so...

301
00:22:05,303 --> 00:22:11,182
why don't you call your boss
and tell him you're going to be late?

302
00:22:11,221 --> 00:22:14,068
- Late?
- You still might make it, Neil.

303
00:22:23,185 --> 00:22:25,388
Karl. Hey, it's Neil.

304
00:22:25,425 --> 00:22:27,147
Yeah, I got delayed.

305
00:22:27,184 --> 00:22:31,241
Abby wasn't feeling so great,
But I'll be there as soon as I can.

306
00:22:31,279 --> 00:22:34,922
No, no. You can give me directions
when I get closer, OK?

307
00:22:34,957 --> 00:22:38,305
Yeah. Yeah, sure. Thanks. Bye.

308
00:22:42,027 --> 00:22:43,848
So what more do you want?

309
00:22:48,234 --> 00:22:49,826
You.

310
00:22:52,008 --> 00:22:53,252
You.

311
00:23:01,125 --> 00:23:02,913
Westside. Now.

312
00:23:05,604 --> 00:23:09,345
Dan, hi. It's Abby.
I don't think I'm going to make it.

313
00:23:28,603 --> 00:23:32,279
Neil, That place over there.

314
00:23:32,315 --> 00:23:34,485
They know me.
I've taken clients there.

315
00:23:35,866 --> 00:23:38,516
Well, now you're taking a new client.

316
00:23:43,319 --> 00:23:45,685
Hi, uh...Mr. Randall.

317
00:23:45,718 --> 00:23:46,862
Good afternoon, sir.

318
00:23:46,902 --> 00:23:48,690
Pleasure to see you again.

319
00:23:48,725 --> 00:23:53,131
Now, um, we have a table for three,
please?

320
00:23:53,172 --> 00:23:55,822
- Right this way.
- May I take your coats?

321
00:23:57,234 --> 00:23:58,182
It's all right.

322
00:24:01,073 --> 00:24:03,112
What can I get you to drink?

323
00:24:03,152 --> 00:24:05,518
Nothing, thank you.

324
00:24:05,552 --> 00:24:08,617
Ahh, good bottle of wine. Red.

325
00:24:08,654 --> 00:24:11,719
- Something around, uh, 200 bucks.
- Yes, sir.

326
00:24:13,069 --> 00:24:14,530
And these prices--

327
00:24:14,572 --> 00:24:16,197
What would you recommend, Neil?

328
00:24:17,739 --> 00:24:19,113
Who do you think you are?

329
00:24:20,074 --> 00:24:21,416
Oh, that's easy.

330
00:24:23,018 --> 00:24:24,806
Right now,

331
00:24:24,841 --> 00:24:27,110
I'm God.

332
00:24:27,144 --> 00:24:29,510
Please just tell us
what you want us to do.

333
00:24:31,719 --> 00:24:34,914
You know, people are always saying
they'd do anything for their kids.

334
00:24:35,910 --> 00:24:36,858
Anything.

335
00:24:38,021 --> 00:24:39,809
So I'm going to put that to the test.

336
00:24:39,844 --> 00:24:43,160
For the next 24 hours, you're mine,
then you get her back, you got it?

337
00:24:43,203 --> 00:24:44,413
Hmm.

338
00:24:45,698 --> 00:24:48,185
- Can I take your order?
- Yeah, I guess--

339
00:24:48,225 --> 00:24:50,199
I guess you got steak in here.

340
00:24:50,241 --> 00:24:52,891
Yes, sir. Steak Dauphinoise.

341
00:24:52,928 --> 00:24:54,520
OK. That'll do. Yeah.

342
00:24:54,560 --> 00:24:57,875
- Um, rare. Thank you.
- Sir?

343
00:24:59,134 --> 00:25:01,238
Oh, they're not eating.

344
00:25:04,572 --> 00:25:05,978
Yeah, that's right.

345
00:25:06,012 --> 00:25:08,182
- You gotta run.
- That's right.

346
00:25:09,754 --> 00:25:11,314
Ahem.

347
00:25:11,354 --> 00:25:13,142
Excuse me.

348
00:25:13,177 --> 00:25:15,184
What do you mean, we've gotta run?

349
00:25:15,224 --> 00:25:18,223
Well, we gotta pay for this somehow.

350
00:25:18,263 --> 00:25:19,408
And I'm all out of cash.

351
00:25:19,447 --> 00:25:20,876
So what are we supposed
to do about that?

352
00:25:20,919 --> 00:25:22,412
You're going to walk
out of here right now.

353
00:25:22,454 --> 00:25:24,340
You're not going to talk
to your buddy on the door,

354
00:25:24,373 --> 00:25:25,321
and you're going to go get some.

355
00:25:27,637 --> 00:25:32,075
and if you're not back here by 5:30
with, say, 300 bucks,

356
00:25:32,115 --> 00:25:35,496
well, you know what they say.

357
00:25:35,537 --> 00:25:38,286
Never pick a fight with someone
who's got nothing to lose.

358
00:25:43,663 --> 00:25:45,124
Run along.

359
00:25:52,940 --> 00:25:54,369
That's good.

360
00:25:54,412 --> 00:25:56,866
- Who you calling?
- Kristin. That designer I met last month.

361
00:25:56,906 --> 00:25:58,531
- Who?
- Kristin.

362
00:25:58,570 --> 00:26:00,903
Will you ever listen to anything I say?
She's 4 blocks from here.

363
00:26:00,937 --> 00:26:02,180
Voicemail. No answer.

364
00:26:02,217 --> 00:26:04,191
There's gotta be someone else
we know around here.

365
00:26:04,232 --> 00:26:05,180
We don't know anyone on this side of town.

366
00:26:05,223 --> 00:26:07,459
How does he know about our lives?
What have we done to him?

367
00:26:07,495 --> 00:26:10,364
We haven't done anything, babe.
Ok? He's just crazy. That's what it is.

368
00:26:10,406 --> 00:26:11,715
Do you know him from work? Tell me.

369
00:26:11,749 --> 00:26:13,091
Is it from accounts?
Somebody you pissed off?

370
00:26:13,125 --> 00:26:16,572
No. What, enough that he'd take our kid?
I don't think so. No way.

371
00:26:16,612 --> 00:26:17,855
We've only got 15 minutes.

372
00:26:17,892 --> 00:26:19,452
- Oh, God.
- Listen to me.

373
00:26:19,491 --> 00:26:21,313
Listen to me.
He's got to get the money.

374
00:26:21,346 --> 00:26:25,371
- Please. Uh, this is important. It's--
- Neil!

375
00:26:26,817 --> 00:26:29,499
- Neil!
- We really need your help.

376
00:26:29,536 --> 00:26:30,550
Please listen to us.

377
00:26:30,591 --> 00:26:34,583
My name is Neil Randall. And, uh,
this is my card. This is my wife.

378
00:26:34,622 --> 00:26:36,312
OK, we need--we need money.

379
00:26:36,349 --> 00:26:38,356
We're not begging.
OK, if you could just--

380
00:26:38,397 --> 00:26:40,022
Oh, I'm late for a meeting.

381
00:26:40,060 --> 00:26:42,002
No. No, you get back.

382
00:26:42,044 --> 00:26:43,604
Our daughter could--

383
00:26:43,643 --> 00:26:45,104
No, don't!

384
00:26:45,146 --> 00:26:47,251
Our daughter could die
if you don't help us.

385
00:26:48,377 --> 00:26:50,743
If you don't take your hands off of me
in the next 2 seconds--

386
00:26:50,777 --> 00:26:52,205
Neil, let him go. Let's go.

387
00:26:52,248 --> 00:26:54,036
I have an idea. I have an idea!

388
00:27:00,181 --> 00:27:02,253
'Scuse me. 'Scuse me.

389
00:27:02,293 --> 00:27:03,722
We need to sell this bracelet.

390
00:27:05,939 --> 00:27:08,208
- I paid 2 grand for that.
- We only need 300.

391
00:27:08,243 --> 00:27:09,191
- Yeah.
- OK.

392
00:27:10,962 --> 00:27:12,750
Come on. We gotta go.

393
00:27:14,513 --> 00:27:16,400
It's a fake. Give you 20 bucks.

394
00:27:17,936 --> 00:27:19,659
What? It's not a fake.

395
00:27:19,695 --> 00:27:21,996
- Are you kidding me?
- Baby, I paid 2 grand for it, OK?

396
00:27:22,030 --> 00:27:23,655
Stop.

397
00:27:23,694 --> 00:27:26,857
I was kidding. Kidding.
I'll give you 200, OK?

398
00:27:26,893 --> 00:27:30,754
- Funny. 300.
- Oh, forget it.

399
00:27:33,226 --> 00:27:36,127
Yeah. Well, there's just one little thing.

400
00:27:37,673 --> 00:27:39,974
I can't forget it.

401
00:27:40,008 --> 00:27:42,211
300. Now.

402
00:27:45,063 --> 00:27:46,753
Come on. We got 2 minutes.

403
00:27:49,253 --> 00:27:50,365
This way.

404
00:27:50,405 --> 00:27:51,386
Aah!

405
00:28:04,544 --> 00:28:06,332
- Where'd he go?
- S-sir?

406
00:28:06,367 --> 00:28:08,603
Where did he go?
He was sitting right there.

407
00:28:08,639 --> 00:28:10,394
I--I'm sorry, sir. I didn't see, um...

408
00:28:10,431 --> 00:28:13,496
- The man, he was sitting right there.
- Uh, I'm sorry, I--

409
00:28:13,533 --> 00:28:15,540
- Come on. You must have!
- Hey.

410
00:28:17,659 --> 00:28:19,764
Dead on time.

411
00:28:21,754 --> 00:28:23,576
Now this place ain't bad.

412
00:28:23,610 --> 00:28:25,781
I might bring the good wife here, huh?

413
00:28:25,817 --> 00:28:28,402
Settle this up, would you, Neil?

414
00:28:28,440 --> 00:28:30,228
'Scuse us.

415
00:28:35,350 --> 00:28:36,909
- So you got it?
- Yeah.

416
00:28:36,950 --> 00:28:38,258
Quite a performance.

417
00:28:38,293 --> 00:28:41,194
Let's see if you can
get to South Frank within 20 from here.

418
00:28:41,236 --> 00:28:43,821
- I need this delivered in person.
- What's this?

419
00:28:43,859 --> 00:28:45,004
- What's going on?
- Go and check the station after it's done.

420
00:28:45,042 --> 00:28:47,594
Just a little errand for Abby, Neil.
Calm down.

421
00:28:47,634 --> 00:28:49,226
- What is it?
- I don't know.

422
00:28:49,266 --> 00:28:49,361
- (Indistinct)
- Easy, hey.

423
00:28:49,361 --> 00:28:51,630
- (Indistinct)
- Easy, hey.

424
00:28:51,664 --> 00:28:53,354
I want to get to know you a little better.

425
00:28:53,392 --> 00:28:54,820
We might have something
in common--

426
00:28:54,863 --> 00:28:56,008
For Christ's sake.

427
00:28:56,047 --> 00:28:58,980
It's all right. Neil. I can do it.

428
00:28:59,022 --> 00:29:00,549
I can deliver a letter, OK?

429
00:29:01,805 --> 00:29:04,106
OK, OK. You go.

430
00:29:04,140 --> 00:29:05,601
Take care, OK?

431
00:29:10,410 --> 00:29:12,831
You're not worried, are you?

432
00:29:12,873 --> 00:29:16,036
She might see a cop.
Start getting ideas.

433
00:29:16,072 --> 00:29:17,119
No, she'll do it.

434
00:29:20,487 --> 00:29:21,435
- Uhh.
- Abby!

435
00:29:21,479 --> 00:29:23,201
Wait. Leave it. Leave it.

436
00:29:23,238 --> 00:29:26,237
- You son of a bitch!
- Just leave it, OK?

437
00:29:26,277 --> 00:29:27,771
All right?

438
00:29:27,813 --> 00:29:30,681
Anger's good, Neil.

439
00:29:30,724 --> 00:29:32,512
Come on.

440
00:29:32,547 --> 00:29:33,757
Come on. Let's go.

441
00:29:33,794 --> 00:29:35,070
Let's go.

442
00:29:38,689 --> 00:29:40,859
Hey!

443
00:29:42,464 --> 00:29:43,478
Hey!

444
00:29:46,430 --> 00:29:47,739
Hey.

445
00:29:52,061 --> 00:29:54,362
One word and your daughter's dead.

446
00:29:56,155 --> 00:29:57,267
- Hey.
- Dad.

447
00:29:59,034 --> 00:30:01,105
It's good to see you, son.
How are you?

448
00:30:01,146 --> 00:30:04,406
- What are you doing here?
- Uh, well, I just, uh...

449
00:30:04,440 --> 00:30:07,603
had to come in for work, and, uh...

450
00:30:07,639 --> 00:30:08,719
Well, what about you?

451
00:30:08,759 --> 00:30:10,646
I mean, I wouldn't expect to see you
on the Westside.

452
00:30:10,678 --> 00:30:12,947
Kory, that girl I met in social studies.

453
00:30:12,981 --> 00:30:15,053
She lives just down the street, so.

454
00:30:15,093 --> 00:30:16,337
Good.

455
00:30:16,372 --> 00:30:17,898
Good.

456
00:30:19,443 --> 00:30:21,101
Is, uh, everything OK?

457
00:30:21,139 --> 00:30:22,415
Yeah, I'm fine.

458
00:30:22,450 --> 00:30:25,167
Oh, just work, job.

459
00:30:25,201 --> 00:30:26,859
I got a lot on my mind and stuff.

460
00:30:26,897 --> 00:30:29,263
Listen, we gotta run.

461
00:30:29,296 --> 00:30:31,684
- I'll catch you later on, OK?
- Yeah, sure.

462
00:30:31,727 --> 00:30:36,199
Could you--
uh, use a ride, or...

463
00:30:36,238 --> 00:30:37,895
- Yeah.
- Neil.

464
00:30:37,933 --> 00:30:40,420
Have you forgotten something?

465
00:30:40,460 --> 00:30:42,314
If you're late?

466
00:30:42,348 --> 00:30:44,486
Huh?

467
00:30:44,523 --> 00:30:45,952
Your wife'll kill you.

468
00:30:45,995 --> 00:30:47,336
Yeah, I forgot.

469
00:30:48,426 --> 00:30:51,491
I'm sorry, son. We're pushed for time.
I'll talk to you later, OK?

470
00:30:51,529 --> 00:30:52,641
Sure.

471
00:31:19,424 --> 00:31:23,034
So you got a child of your own
and you put us through this.

472
00:31:25,757 --> 00:31:28,025
What's he going to think
of the two of you when this comes out?

473
00:31:38,074 --> 00:31:39,535
Have you thought about that?

474
00:31:49,877 --> 00:31:52,332
Hey, what's he going to think, huh?

475
00:31:52,373 --> 00:31:55,372
Tell me. Come on.

476
00:31:55,411 --> 00:31:56,621
What's he going to think?

477
00:31:56,659 --> 00:31:59,658
What's he going to tell Kory when mom
and dad are on the evening news?

478
00:31:59,699 --> 00:32:01,487
Have you thought about that?

479
00:32:01,521 --> 00:32:03,211
Well, have you?

480
00:32:07,759 --> 00:32:09,547
What the hell are you doing?

481
00:32:16,268 --> 00:32:17,544
Uhh.

482
00:32:21,195 --> 00:32:22,569
How's everything going at work?

483
00:32:29,160 --> 00:32:31,428
I hear advertising's a cutthroat business.

484
00:32:31,464 --> 00:32:32,870
A lot of pressure.

485
00:32:36,390 --> 00:32:38,080
Is that why you screw up
so many people's lives?

486
00:32:38,117 --> 00:32:40,484
What are you talking about?

487
00:32:41,476 --> 00:32:42,424
Recognize that place?

488
00:32:44,227 --> 00:32:46,332
Fifth floor. Straight ahead.

489
00:32:47,522 --> 00:32:49,627
That's the head office
of Magris Industries.

490
00:32:49,665 --> 00:32:52,031
You've heard of them?

491
00:32:52,065 --> 00:32:54,301
Of course you have.

492
00:32:54,336 --> 00:32:56,757
And with this million dollar launch
coming up,

493
00:32:56,799 --> 00:32:59,962
I'm sure this is something
you'd want to keep under wraps.

