00:51:13,171 --> 00:51:14,764
Hit the big time...

753
00:51:52,198 --> 00:51:53,245
Shit.

754
00:52:33,241 --> 00:52:34,833
Oh, oh, shit.

755
00:52:47,508 --> 00:52:48,456
Yeah?

756
00:52:48,499 --> 00:52:50,440
Missing you already.

757
00:52:50,483 --> 00:52:53,199
I made it. I'm at the clock tower.

758
00:52:53,234 --> 00:52:54,663
Too late.

759
00:52:54,706 --> 00:52:58,414
No, no, no, I did what you asked.
I--I--I got here.

760
00:52:58,448 --> 00:53:00,269
You're too late.

761
00:53:00,304 --> 00:53:02,986
Jesus Christ.
What do you want from me?

762
00:53:03,023 --> 00:53:05,389
It's not all bad.
I'll let you say good-bye.

763
00:53:05,421 --> 00:53:07,493
What? No, wait.

764
00:53:10,092 --> 00:53:11,979
- Neil? Neil?
- Baby, listen.

765
00:53:12,012 --> 00:53:14,945
- Neil, listen, he's got--
- Time's up.

766
00:53:14,987 --> 00:53:17,287
W-where are you?

767
00:53:17,322 --> 00:53:20,004
W-what are you going to do?

768
00:53:20,041 --> 00:53:21,950
Come and take a look, Neil.

769
00:53:24,200 --> 00:53:26,588
- Where?
- The edge, Neil.

770
00:53:26,631 --> 00:53:29,314
Just step up to the edge
and look down.

771
00:53:41,986 --> 00:53:43,230
OK...OK...

772
00:53:43,265 --> 00:53:46,046
You're not scared, are you?

773
00:53:46,080 --> 00:53:48,981
A little bird told me
you're not crazy about heights.

774
00:53:49,023 --> 00:53:51,739
I'm at the edge.
I'm at the goddamn edge!

775
00:53:51,775 --> 00:53:53,781
Abby really wanted one last look.

776
00:53:53,821 --> 00:53:56,025
- No, wait, wait.
- But if you haven't got the balls--

777
00:53:56,061 --> 00:53:57,883
I can't even see you.

778
00:53:57,916 --> 00:54:00,566
You're not at the edge, Neil,
or we'd see you.

779
00:54:00,604 --> 00:54:02,970
- I want to see you standing.
- Wait, wait!

780
00:54:08,185 --> 00:54:10,094
OK, OK, I--

781
00:54:10,136 --> 00:54:13,037
- I see you.
- Stand up, Neil.

782
00:54:13,079 --> 00:54:14,159
No...

783
00:54:14,199 --> 00:54:15,792
- Get up.
- No.

784
00:54:15,830 --> 00:54:18,163
- Neil, get up.
- Please, don't do this.

785
00:54:20,021 --> 00:54:21,875
Be a real man for once in your life.

786
00:54:25,427 --> 00:54:26,855
Unh...

787
00:54:37,711 --> 00:54:38,888
I'm here.

788
00:54:38,927 --> 00:54:41,992
I'm...

789
00:54:42,030 --> 00:54:43,590
Tell him to move back.
It's too dangerous.

790
00:54:43,629 --> 00:54:45,832
- I'm on the edge.
- (Indistinct)

791
00:54:45,869 --> 00:54:47,526
Tell him to move back. That's enough!

792
00:54:47,564 --> 00:54:49,286
No, please, he'll kill himself.

793
00:54:49,323 --> 00:54:50,632
That's enough! Listen to me!

794
00:54:50,667 --> 00:54:52,554
No!

795
00:54:52,586 --> 00:54:54,887
- Don't you touch her!
- Get in the car.

796
00:54:56,361 --> 00:54:58,270
Stay in here. Stay in there.

797
00:55:00,616 --> 00:55:03,615
Listen, it doesn't matter
that you were late.

798
00:55:03,655 --> 00:55:05,476
I was going to have her anyway.

799
00:55:05,510 --> 00:55:08,095
Only she doesn't know that yet.

800
00:55:10,916 --> 00:55:14,592
Why are you doing this?
Why are you doing this to me?

801
00:55:14,626 --> 00:55:17,473
Why? Why...

802
00:55:19,521 --> 00:55:21,081
Haven't you seen it yet?

803
00:55:21,121 --> 00:55:22,527
Huh, Neil?

804
00:55:22,560 --> 00:55:24,021
What are you talking about?

805
00:55:24,064 --> 00:55:25,624
The answer is up there.

806
00:55:27,710 --> 00:55:31,255
Ah, it's right there. Look around.

807
00:55:31,293 --> 00:55:34,391
- Where?
- It's under your nose.

808
00:55:34,428 --> 00:55:38,005
Come on, you want
to know why, don't you?

809
00:55:42,777 --> 00:55:44,151
Aah!

810
00:55:52,630 --> 00:55:54,768
What does it mean?

811
00:55:54,806 --> 00:55:57,107
I'll tell you what it means.

812
00:55:57,141 --> 00:56:00,042
It means stamping out a problem.

813
00:56:00,083 --> 00:56:01,806
Crushing it.

814
00:56:01,844 --> 00:56:04,232
So, now I've got
your daughter and your wife.

815
00:56:06,097 --> 00:56:11,213
And you're just a tiny dot in the sky
worth nothing.

816
00:56:11,248 --> 00:56:15,524
Please, no, I'm begging you, don't.

817
00:56:15,567 --> 00:56:18,533
And what exactly am I going to do?

818
00:56:18,573 --> 00:56:21,606
I'll leave that to your imagination, Neil.

819
00:56:21,645 --> 00:56:24,295
Don't you hang up! Don't you hang up!

820
00:56:24,331 --> 00:56:26,720
Sweet dreams.

821
00:56:30,537 --> 00:56:32,871
A-Abby!

822
00:56:32,905 --> 00:56:34,083
Abby!

823
00:57:25,751 --> 00:57:27,343
- Hey, whoa!
- I need help.

824
00:57:27,383 --> 00:57:29,870
- Yeah, the line's back there, sir.
- No, this is an emergency.

825
00:57:29,910 --> 00:57:32,560
My--my wife and child
have been kidnapped.

826
00:57:32,597 --> 00:57:34,123
There's a psycho out there,

827
00:57:34,165 --> 00:57:37,425
OK, he--he's taken
my wife and my little girl.

828
00:57:37,460 --> 00:57:40,720
You got my car, he's driving my car.
He--it's a Range Rover,

829
00:57:40,754 --> 00:57:44,233
"R"-"U", uh, 83--83 "A."

830
00:57:44,273 --> 00:57:47,120
And there--he's got
a woman who's helping him. She's--

831
00:57:47,153 --> 00:57:48,559
Pretending to be a sitter?

832
00:57:48,592 --> 00:57:51,078
Randall, right?
Your name is Neil Randall?

833
00:57:51,119 --> 00:57:54,151
- Yeah.
- I just spoke to your wife.

834
00:57:54,190 --> 00:57:56,328
- She was here.
- What?

835
00:57:58,221 --> 00:58:01,035
- W-wait, when?
- About half an hour ago.

836
00:58:05,194 --> 00:58:06,208
You spoke--
you spoke to my wife?

837
00:58:06,250 --> 00:58:07,559
- Yeah.
- She's OK?

838
00:58:07,593 --> 00:58:10,048
- She explained the whole thing.
- OK.

839
00:58:10,089 --> 00:58:13,023
She said that
you might show up with this story.

840
00:58:13,064 --> 00:58:15,551
At the state you're in,
you'll try anything to stop her.

841
00:58:18,310 --> 00:58:19,935
Stop her doing what?

842
00:58:19,973 --> 00:58:21,566
Leaving you.

843
00:58:22,852 --> 00:58:26,081
No, you don't understand.

844
00:58:26,115 --> 00:58:28,286
No, she's not leaving me.

845
00:58:28,323 --> 00:58:30,232
No, he made her say that.

846
00:58:30,274 --> 00:58:31,768
OK? He's got
the whole thing planned.

847
00:58:31,810 --> 00:58:34,526
He's smart. Oh, he--
he's smart, all right.

848
00:58:34,560 --> 00:58:36,861
He, uh--he's got our daughter.

849
00:58:36,896 --> 00:58:41,335
And he's made us--
forced us to do everything he says.

850
00:58:41,374 --> 00:58:41,501
Look, I get it. I know how you feel.

851
00:58:41,501 --> 00:58:43,639
Look, I get it. I know how you feel.

852
00:58:43,675 --> 00:58:45,976
My wife left me a year ago.

853
00:58:46,010 --> 00:58:48,311
I went a bit--crazy myself.

854
00:58:48,346 --> 00:58:50,287
I'm not some
jealous husband, all right?

855
00:58:50,329 --> 00:58:53,111
I'm the victim of a crime!

856
00:58:56,055 --> 00:58:58,901
Look, you've been drinking.

857
00:58:58,934 --> 00:59:03,602
I'm not drunk. He did this to me.

858
00:59:03,637 --> 00:59:07,596
Do yourself a favor.
Go home, sober up.

859
00:59:07,635 --> 00:59:10,351
Try and accept it, all right?

860
00:59:10,387 --> 00:59:14,477
Nothing for me to do. Can't help you.
All right?

861
00:59:14,513 --> 00:59:17,546
Let's go, I'll walk you out.

862
01:00:41,524 --> 01:00:43,411
It's all right. Oh!

863
01:00:43,443 --> 01:00:44,458
- Oh, baby.
- It's OK!

864
01:00:44,499 --> 01:00:45,513
- It's OK.
- Are you OK?

865
01:00:45,555 --> 01:00:47,943
- He didn't touch me.
- You promise me?

866
01:00:47,986 --> 01:00:49,163
Yes, I promise.

867
01:00:56,271 --> 01:00:57,929
He made me lie to that cop.

868
01:00:57,967 --> 01:00:59,876
I thought you were going
to fall off the building.

869
01:00:59,918 --> 01:01:02,022
I thought you were going to die.

870
01:01:02,062 --> 01:01:03,044
Oh, baby.

871
01:01:03,085 --> 01:01:04,328
Oh, baby I thought I'd lost you.

872
01:01:04,365 --> 01:01:06,698
I thought--

873
01:01:06,732 --> 01:01:08,870
- I thought I'd lost everything.
- It's OK.

874
01:01:08,907 --> 01:01:10,216
Remember that feeling!

875
01:01:12,362 --> 01:01:15,525
'Cause the next time I tell you to do
something you're going to do it, right?

876
01:01:17,257 --> 01:01:19,361
Right, Mr. Randall?

877
01:01:21,351 --> 01:01:23,489
Good, now we understand
each other.

878
01:01:23,527 --> 01:01:25,348
Get in the back.

879
01:01:37,025 --> 01:01:39,807
Why don't we just do it?
Whatever it is.

880
01:01:42,112 --> 01:01:43,225
Yeah.

881
01:02:09,815 --> 01:02:11,407
I love you, Abby.

882
01:02:13,014 --> 01:02:14,606
You know that, right?

883
01:02:19,828 --> 01:02:22,412
Look what it takes
for us to get this close.

884
01:02:26,866 --> 01:02:30,028
You guess where you're going yet?

885
01:02:30,064 --> 01:02:32,583
Just tell us.

886
01:02:32,624 --> 01:02:34,445
We're going where you
were going all along.

887
01:02:36,942 --> 01:02:38,534
We're going to meet the boss.

888
01:02:40,333 --> 01:02:41,609
The top man.

889
01:02:43,468 --> 01:02:44,776
Karl Granger.

890
01:02:52,873 --> 01:02:55,043
I knew it had something
to do with work.

891
01:02:57,255 --> 01:02:59,710
Maybe.

892
01:02:59,751 --> 01:03:03,263
Jesus. I don't know anything, anymore.

893
01:03:05,316 --> 01:03:07,225
Home sweet home.

894
01:03:28,765 --> 01:03:30,520
You first, now.

895
01:03:30,556 --> 01:03:32,149
Just ease the way.

896
01:03:34,427 --> 01:03:36,248
What do I tell him?

897
01:03:36,282 --> 01:03:38,550
Just tell him the truth.

898
01:03:40,537 --> 01:03:41,518
Get out.

899
01:03:41,561 --> 01:03:43,415
Just do it.

900
01:04:08,112 --> 01:04:09,158
Hey, Neil.

901
01:04:15,693 --> 01:04:17,318
There something
I forgot to ask you.

902
01:04:17,356 --> 01:04:18,785
What?

903
01:04:18,828 --> 01:04:20,584
How far would you go?

904
01:04:20,620 --> 01:04:23,205
What?

905
01:04:23,243 --> 01:04:25,631
To save the things
most important to you.

906
01:04:25,673 --> 01:04:26,720
How far?

907
01:04:26,762 --> 01:04:30,109
I would do whatever it takes
to protect my family.

908
01:04:30,153 --> 01:04:32,094
Yeah, I can understand that.

909
01:04:32,136 --> 01:04:34,274
And that's a great thing.

910
01:04:34,311 --> 01:04:36,481
There's this one last thing
I want you to do.

911
01:04:44,388 --> 01:04:45,631
Go on.

912
01:04:50,785 --> 01:04:52,857
I want you to kill, Neil.

913
01:04:54,464 --> 01:04:56,318
You wanted to know
what this was all about.

914
01:04:56,352 --> 01:04:59,133
Well, this is it.

915
01:05:01,502 --> 01:05:05,178
No. You are crazy. I can't do that.

916
01:05:05,213 --> 01:05:06,554
You don't have to.

917
01:05:08,507 --> 01:05:10,776
But if you don't...

918
01:05:10,811 --> 01:05:12,436
You'll never see Sophie again.

919
01:05:13,594 --> 01:05:15,481
Because believe one thing,

920
01:05:15,514 --> 01:05:19,571
I don't give a damn
what happens to me.

921
01:05:21,143 --> 01:05:22,255
I can't--I can't--

922
01:05:22,295 --> 01:05:23,636
Neil, there's no debate here, OK?

923
01:05:23,670 --> 01:05:27,084
There's one person in that house and if
they're not dead in the next 10 minutes,

924
01:05:27,126 --> 01:05:28,270
someone else will be.

925
01:05:33,300 --> 01:05:36,016
Have you forgotten
that feeling already?

926
01:05:39,121 --> 01:05:40,714
10 minutes.

927
01:08:08,608 --> 01:08:10,811
Oh, Jesus.

928
01:08:10,847 --> 01:08:12,602
You scared the life out of me.

929
01:08:14,334 --> 01:08:15,413
Judy?

930
01:08:15,453 --> 01:08:17,656
I just took a shower.

931
01:08:17,693 --> 01:08:19,699
I was beginning to think
you weren't going to make it.

932
01:08:22,300 --> 01:08:23,892
Mmm.

933
01:08:25,083 --> 01:08:26,643
God, Neil, you look awful.

934
01:08:26,682 --> 01:08:28,023
What happened?

935
01:08:29,785 --> 01:08:31,956
You were stuck with Abby
when you called, weren't you?

936
01:08:31,992 --> 01:08:33,585
Is she OK?

937
01:08:36,183 --> 01:08:39,793
Yeah. She's OK.

938
01:08:39,830 --> 01:08:43,920
Well, she bought all that stuff
about going to Karl's, didn't she?

939
01:08:43,956 --> 01:08:46,476
Yeah, she trusts me.

940
01:08:48,626 --> 01:08:50,219
Yeah.

941
01:08:51,538 --> 01:08:53,708
Anyways, let's get this jacket off.

942
01:08:53,745 --> 01:08:54,857
No, no.

943
01:08:57,104 --> 01:08:58,510
It's cold out there.

944
01:08:59,983 --> 01:09:01,509
OK.

945
01:09:01,551 --> 01:09:03,339
Well, come in by the fire, then.

946
01:09:06,541 --> 01:09:07,653
The usual?

947
01:09:08,972 --> 01:09:11,208
Yeah--yeah, thanks.

948
01:09:16,361 --> 01:09:18,848
So, how did you find the place?

949
01:09:18,888 --> 01:09:20,448
I thought you were going to call.

950
01:09:23,207 --> 01:09:24,832
I know what's wrong.

951
01:09:24,871 --> 01:09:26,757
It's a long drive,

952
01:09:26,790 --> 01:09:28,993
plenty of time
to discover a conscience.

953
01:09:31,844 --> 01:09:34,975
Look, Neil, don't you
think I felt guilty, too?

954
01:09:35,011 --> 01:09:39,614
But we've had all these months
of watching our backs.

955
01:09:39,649 --> 01:09:43,194
Going to our little French restaurant,
in the afternoons.

956
01:09:43,232 --> 01:09:46,711
Now, finally, we can just relax
and enjoy each other.

957
01:09:46,752 --> 01:09:47,864
Right?

958
01:09:49,535 --> 01:09:51,127
I don't know.

959
01:09:51,165 --> 01:09:52,278
Neil.

960
01:09:54,140 --> 01:09:56,212
Neil?

961
01:09:59,195 --> 01:10:02,390
- Look, have I done something wrong?
- No.

962
01:10:03,706 --> 01:10:05,909
- Well, then, what is it?
- It's nothing.

963
01:10:05,945 --> 01:10:07,984
Well, it's got to be something.

964
01:10:17,525 --> 01:10:19,117
Who is that?

965
01:10:20,596 --> 01:10:22,505
That's my husband Tom.

966
01:10:25,266 --> 01:10:27,654
I guess now you can put a face
to the name.

967
01:10:31,505 --> 01:10:32,879
Where is he right now?

968
01:10:32,912 --> 01:10:36,042
You know where he is.
He's on that hunting trip.

969
01:10:36,079 --> 01:10:37,671
That's why we're here.

970
01:10:39,245 --> 01:10:42,790
God, anyway, what's
with the sudden interest in Tom?

971
01:10:42,828 --> 01:10:43,842
You've never given a damn before--

972
01:10:43,885 --> 01:10:45,793
What do you think
he would do, if he found out?

973
01:10:45,836 --> 01:10:47,624
He's not going to find out.

974
01:10:47,659 --> 01:10:49,219
Answer me!
Just what would Tom do?

975
01:10:49,258 --> 01:10:51,330
I don't know what he'd do.

976
01:10:51,369 --> 01:10:53,638
It would destroy him.

977
01:10:53,673 --> 01:10:55,233
Christ!

978
01:10:55,272 --> 01:10:57,410
Why are we even talking about this?

979
01:10:57,448 --> 01:10:59,935
He's got Sophie.

980
01:10:59,975 --> 01:11:01,349
What?!

981
01:11:01,382 --> 01:11:04,131
Your husband has my child!

982
01:11:04,165 --> 01:11:05,957
Why would Tom have Sophie? What--

983
01:11:05,957 --> 01:11:07,167
Why would Tom have Sophie? What--

984
01:11:07,205 --> 01:11:09,440
Because he knows about us!

985
01:11:10,500 --> 01:11:13,630
- What?
- He knows everything, Judy.

986
01:11:15,457 --> 01:11:17,180
Tom knows.

987
01:11:17,218 --> 01:11:18,810
Baby.

988
01:11:18,848 --> 01:11:20,441
He's going to kill her.

989
01:11:20,480 --> 01:11:22,367
- What?
- If I don't...

990
01:11:22,399 --> 01:11:25,715
If you--if you don't what? What?

991
01:11:25,759 --> 01:11:28,147
Baby, you're scaring me.

992
01:11:29,405 --> 01:11:32,665
He says, he's going to kill her--

993
01:11:32,700 --> 01:11:33,976
- What are you--
- If I don't--

994
01:11:34,011 --> 01:11:35,124
Doing with a...

995
01:11:35,163 --> 01:11:36,689
No!

996
01:11:36,730 --> 01:11:38,257
No!

997
01:11:38,298 --> 01:11:39,607
Neil, don't!

998
01:11:39,642 --> 01:11:42,325
Get off of me!

999
01:11:42,361 --> 01:11:44,564
No! No!

1000
01:11:54,613 --> 01:11:56,717
I can't. I can't.

1001
01:12:06,001 --> 01:12:07,081
Do it!

1002
01:12:09,264 --> 01:12:10,572
Tom!

1003
01:12:10,608 --> 01:12:12,811
Do it, Neil.

1004
01:12:12,846 --> 01:12:14,820
I can't!

1005
01:12:16,110 --> 01:12:19,011
- No?
- I can't.

1006
01:12:20,301 --> 01:12:23,616
- Well, I can.
- No!

1007
01:12:23,659 --> 01:12:24,968
A life for a life.

1008
01:12:25,003 --> 01:12:27,075
Just one little number.

1009
01:12:30,441 --> 01:12:32,262
Do it, now. Do it, now.

1010
01:12:32,296 --> 01:12:34,084
- Tom!
- No!

1011
01:12:34,120 --> 01:12:35,581
Now! Do it!

1012
01:12:38,982 --> 01:12:40,476
No!

1013
01:12:42,053 --> 01:12:47,037
- I'm sorry.
